		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2014"></a><br><code>sle2014/paper19</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2014</a> paper:</span><br><i>Test-Data Generation for Xtext (Tool Paper)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JohannesHärtel.html">Johannes Härtel</a>, <a href="../profile/LukasHärtel.html">Lukas Härtel</a>, <a href="../profile/RalfLämmel.html">Ralf Lämmel</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_19">10.1007/978-3-319-11245-9_19</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagM">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> The contribution is a method and tool for grammar-based test-data generation for Xtext languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It targets tooling support around Xtext language development and testing.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3b.html"><span class="tagL">T3B: Transformation Languages</span></a><ul><li> It uses a DSL for grammar transformation to customize grammars for test-data generation.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It relies on grammatical structure (parse trees/choices) and language descriptions to drive generation.
</li></ul></li></ul>
